# Observability Conventions

## Metric Naming (Prometheus)
- Use `snake_case` with unit suffix: `_total`, `_seconds`, `_bytes`
- Counters end in `_total`: `scenario_runs_total`, `http_requests_total`
- Histograms end in `_seconds` or `_bytes`: `scenario_run_duration_seconds`
- Labels: lowercase snake_case — `status_code`, `scenario_type`, NOT `statusCode`
- Register all metrics in `src/metrics/metrics.registry.ts` — never create inline

## Structured Logging (pino)
Every log entry MUST include:
```typescript
logger.info({
  msg: 'Human-readable description',     // required
  scenarioType: dto.type,                // domain context
  scenarioId: run.id,                    // entity id when available
  duration: durationMs,                  // timing in ms
  // err: error,                         // add for warn/error levels
});
```
- Use `logger.info` for successful operations
- Use `logger.warn` for expected degradation (slow requests, validation errors)
- Use `logger.error` for unhandled exceptions (always include `err` field)
- NEVER log sensitive data (tokens, passwords, PII)

## Sentry
- Call `Sentry.captureException(error)` in every `catch` block for system errors
- Call `Sentry.addBreadcrumb()` for non-fatal events (validation errors)
- Always add context: `{ tags: { scenarioType }, extra: { duration } }`
- Initialize once in `main.ts`, check `process.env.SENTRY_DSN` exists first

## When adding a new endpoint
1. Add metric increment after each business operation
2. Add pino log at the start (debug) and end (info/warn/error)
3. Add Sentry capture in error path
4. Expose new metric labels in Prometheus scrape
